adjectives.description: occulted (comparative more occulted, superlative most occulted)

examples: Over the last eighteen years, America has quietly created an occulted imperium, quite distinct from the sprawling system of military and naval facilities through which America exerts physical force, based not on high politics, but on control of apparently apolitical plumbing facilities.

entries.meaning: (astronomy) Concealed, as by a body coming between.
examples: Each half-occulted star beneath that lies;

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of occult
